abstract: Councilman Corey Johnson seems intent to help the Council assert its independence from the mayor, bringing an ambition to stretch its power of legislation.
snippet: Councilman Corey Johnson seems intent to help the Council assert its independence from the mayor, bringing an ambition to stretch its power of legislation.
lead_paragraph: After a formal vote on Wednesday, Corey Johnson is expected to become the next speaker of the New York City Council, a position second only to the mayor in terms of direct control over the most central political conflicts of city life: real estate development and the budget.

abstract: As he starts his second term, Mayor Bill de Blasio sets aside Clinton centrism in favor of Sanders-style progressivism.
snippet: As he starts his second term, Mayor Bill de Blasio sets aside Clinton centrism in favor of Sanders-style progressivism.
lead_paragraph: You dance with the one that brung ya, as the saying goes, but Bill de Blasio sees no reason to embrace the maxim. Bill and Hillary Clinton gave him a vital kick-start in politics and, fittingly, Mr. de Blasio chose the former president to swear him in as New York’s 109th mayor four years ago. Times change. For his second inaugural, on Monday, the Clintons were well in his rearview mirror.

headline_main: ‘A New Progressive Era’ in New York City

abstract: Addresses by the comptroller, Scott M. Stringer, and public advocate, Letitia James, marked a kind of unofficial start to the 2021 mayoral campaign.
snippet: Addresses by the comptroller, Scott M. Stringer, and public advocate, Letitia James, marked a kind of unofficial start to the 2021 mayoral campaign.
lead_paragraph: If the second inauguration of Mayor Bill de Blasio on Monday lacked some of the excitement of his first go-round, the undercard at the event — a pair of speeches by the newly re-elected comptroller, Scott M. Stringer, and the public advocate, Letitia A. James — provided at least a hint of dramatic tension.

abstract: Colleges are crucial to American greatness but found themselves on the defensive in 2017.
snippet: Colleges are crucial to American greatness but found themselves on the defensive in 2017.
lead_paragraph: When all was said and done, the tax overhaul that President Trump signed into law a little more than a week ago didn’t beat up on higher education to the extent that earlier drafts of the legislation did. Americans who were deducting interest on student loans will still be able to do so. The tuition waivers that many graduate students receive won’t be treated as income.

abstract: Some drivers in Queens and Brooklyn worry their commuting costs could go up with a new congestion plan. They oppose tolls on the East River bridges.
snippet: Some drivers in Queens and Brooklyn worry their commuting costs could go up with a new congestion plan. They oppose tolls on the East River bridges.
lead_paragraph: The closest subway station to Bob Friedrich’s home in eastern Queens is 10 miles away, so he drives to work in Manhattan at least three times a week.

headline_main: For Congestion Pricing Plan, New Support and Steadfast Critics
headline_print_headline: Support Rises, but Critics Are Firm, as Congestion Pricing Gets New Look

abstract: With Mayor de Blasio having alienated some luminaries who attended his first inauguration, his second swearing-in will have a pared-down look.
snippet: With Mayor de Blasio having alienated some luminaries who attended his first inauguration, his second swearing-in will have a pared-down look.
lead_paragraph: When Bill de Blasio was sworn in for his first term as mayor, before a crowd of thousands on Jan. 1, 2014, the event seemed like a political coronation, celebrating New York City’s return to Democratic rule.
